

When call is execture it takes the memory addr of the next instruction and pushes it onto the stack

Once the ret instruction is called it will pop that value off the stack and into EIP and continue from where EIP is

Sometimes the procedure can change flags or registers and cause issues for the mail application. This can be negated in the below options

Saving/Restoring Registers:

  PUSHAD: pushes all contents of the registers onto the stack
  POPAD: restores all of contents of each register from the stack
  
Saving/Restoring Flags:

  PUSHFD: pushes all flags onto the stack
  POPFD: pops the values of the flags off the stack and reassigns the flags
  
